    <dcterms:creator>Vapo-Cresolene Company</dcterms:creator>
    <dcterms:created>1879/1899</dcterms:created>
    <dcterms:description>Vaporizing lamp, including stand, movable cup, globe, and wick, with commercial packaging. The Vapo-Cesolene lamp was designed to vaporize chemical substances, such as cresolene, a by-product of coal-tar used as a disinfectant, by suspending the substance in a metal dish over a flame. The device was used to alleviate respiratory symptoms such as cough and asthma.</dcterms:description>
